<p align="center"><font color="#0E024D" face="Arial"><strong>PLAYER SUBMITTED STRATEGY</strong></font></p>
<div align="center"><center>

  <div align="center"><center><table border="0" width="90%">
    <tr>
      <td>
      <center><font face="Arial"><strong><b><font color="#800000">20-24 THE HERMIT WAY: GOOD LOOT, GOOD EXPERIENCE.</b></font> - <small>Hermitslayer, Xegony</small></strong></font><font face="Arial"></center>
<div align="center"><center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="80%">
  <tr>
    <td>
    <small><hr size="1" color="#C0C0C0"><P>
    In South Karana, at approx. loc -5500, -2700, there is a house surrounded by a stone wall. Every 6 minutes or so, a hermit will spawn inside. Killing him does not affect any factions, he drops fine steel weapons and up to a plat and a half in loot, and the experience is amazing. Also, this is one of the few places enchanters can solo at virtually no risk to themselves. Here's how:<p>
He spawns inside the house, and the door is unopenable, so you'll have to either say, "I want to kill you.", or cast an area effect spell, such as color flux. When he comes out, stun him, tashani him, then Chase the Moon him. All the while, your pet is beating on him. Because his house is enclosed by this stone fence, he'll just start running into the wall. DoT, nuke, nuke, and whenever he breaks fear, just refresh it. You might want to get a clarity before you start, but he never goes agro on you, so you can decide when to kill him. I enjoy having a druid in my party for track (to tell when he spawns -- you can't see through the walls of his house), but it's not necessary. Every couple of minutes, stand up, stand next to the house and cast color flux. If you think he's spawned, but color flux didn't hit him, run around to the other side of the house and cast. He hits reasonably hard, and can heal himself (probably a Paladin), but he should never, ever stand a chance against you. Take your bag of fine steel to the store every once in a while, and you'll be fine.<p>
-Hermitslayer
    </small></font></p>
    <p><small><font face="Arial">&nbsp;</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><center><hr size="1" color="#C0C0C0"><p align="center"><small><strong><font face="Arial">
